{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-post-template-js","path":"/css-in-js-mdx","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"blurb":"Frontend Engineer @ LaunchDarkly. Book addict and tea lover. Passionate about react graphql and making things simple and fast."}},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Mdx is cool. It lets you use react components in markdown files, like markdown on steroids.</p>\n<p>If you use mdx and want to use css in js inside your mdx files, here's a way to do it. Note that\nI can only make this work with the <code class=\"language-text\">styled</code> object and can't make it work with the css prop. The\ncss prop relies on the jsx pragma, which I think requires further tinkering or configuration\nto make it work with storybook and mdx. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"markdown\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-markdown line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-markdown\">import { Meta, Story, Preview } from '@storybook/addon-docs/blocks'\nimport { styled } from '@storybook/theming'\nimport { Alert } from './Alert'\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- \n1. Declare your styled component. You must export the const!\n--></span>\nexport const StyledDiv = styled.div`\n  font-size: 40px;\n  padding-bottom: 10px;\n`\n\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Meta</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">title</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>MDX/Alert<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">component</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span>{Alert}/</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token title important\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">#</span> Alert</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- \n2. Use your styled component as usual. That's it!\n--></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>StyledDiv</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  Hello css in js! We got emotion in mdx!\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>StyledDiv</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Preview</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Story</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">name</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>Success<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Alert</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">kind</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>success<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n           Successfully used emotion css-in-js with mdx!\n        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>Alert</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>Story</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>Preview</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<hr>","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"date":"May 20, 2020","path":"/css-in-js-mdx","title":"Using css in js with mdx","files":[{"name":"hero","publicURL":"/static/hero-b61fbbd3836769868edcda36453eafd2.png"}],"tags":["mdx","css","emotion","styled","components","css-in-js","in","cssinjs","js","react","javascript","storybook","markdown"]}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false}}}